Install package executable launchers

USAGE:
    ir tool install [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] [--bin-dir <dir>] [--force] <pkg-ref>

`ir tool install` resolves <pkg-ref>, scans that package's exec directory
for files whose shebang names Rscript or Rapp, and writes lightweight
launchers into <dir>. Installed launchers are isolated: R_LIBS points at
the resolved ir cache library and R_LIBS_USER is set to NULL.

OPTIONS:
    --with <pkg>  Add a dependency for installed launchers, resolved
                  alongside the provider package. May be repeated and
                  accepts a comma-separated list.
    --r-version <spec>
                  Select the R version for installed launchers with rig.
    --bin-dir <dir>
                  Directory where launchers are written. Defaults to
                  IR_TOOL_BIN_DIR, RAPP_BIN_DIR, XDG_BIN_HOME,
                  XDG_DATA_HOME/../bin, or ~/.local/bin on Unix.
    --force       Overwrite an existing launcher path.

ENVIRONMENT:
    IR_CACHE_DIR      override the cache dir (default: tools::R_user_dir("ir", "cache"))
    IR_RSCRIPT        path to the Rscript executable (default: Rscript on PATH)
    IR_TOOL_BIN_DIR   default launcher install directory
